title: Madame Moitessier (Seated)
significance_text: An iconic synthesis of line, surface and poise; Ingres’ neoclassical ideal of grace and dignity.

title: Madame Moitessier (Standing)
significance_text: A companion portrait that amplifies Ingres’ linear elegance and ornamental detail.

title: Emma Hamilton as a Sibyl
significance_text: Celebrates feminine intellect and charisma by one of the most celebrated women painters of her era.

title: Portrait of Countess Skavronskaia
significance_text: A luminous portrait balancing social presence and psychological immediacy.

title: Summer (La Femme à l’ombrelle)
significance_text: A virtuoso meditation on fabric, gesture and modern leisure in late 19th‑century society.

title: Beata Beatrix
significance_text: A spiritual image of love and loss; a cornerstone of Pre‑Raphaelite symbolism.

title: Proserpine
significance_text: Myth, desire and captivity distilled into a haunting, emblematic portrait.

title: Nanna
significance_text: Austere harmony and introspection typical of late Romantic classicism.

title: Die Venezianerin
significance_text: A Venetian reverie—poised elegance meeting luminous restraint.

title: A Young Woman
significance_text: Quiet modernity—an intimate register of poise and personality.

title: Brown Eyes
significance_text: Natural light and frank presence—British realism at human scale.

title: Lady with Dove
significance_text: A gentle emblem of care; gesture becomes a language of peace.

title: Elaine and Lancelot
significance_text: Pre‑Raphaelite clarity and medieval sentiment intertwined in lyrical detail.

title: Lady Bampfylde
significance_text: Grand manner portraiture that shaped British taste and public imagination.

title: Gretchen
significance_text: A theatrical hush—poised profile and narrative suggestion.

title: Ginevra de’ Benci (study / ref)
significance_text: Early psychological portraiture; subtle modeling of presence that shaped Western art.

title: Emma Hart as Circe
significance_text: Celebrity, theatre and myth converge in an image of magnetic agency.

title: The Singer
significance_text: Velvety finish and poised gesture—an image tuned to lyrical attention.
